What happens to the benchmark if we do:
```suggestion
/-- A nonempty preorder with no maximal element is infinite.
This instance has lower priority to avoid the cycle `Infinite Œ± ‚Üí Nontrivial Œ± ‚Üí Nonempty Œ±` if possible.
-/
instance (priority := 100) NoMaxOrder.infinite [Nonempty Œ±] [NoMaxOrder Œ±] : Infinite Œ± :=
```

... and also:
```suggestion
/-- A nonempty preorder with no minimal element is infinite.
This instance has lower priority to avoid the cycle `Infinite Œ± ‚Üí Nontrivial Œ± ‚Üí Nonempty Œ±` if possible.
-/
instance (priority := 100) NoMinOrder.infinite [Nonempty Œ±] [NoMinOrder Œ±] : Infinite Œ± :=
```
